The White House is celebrating International Day of the Girl by recognizing the leadership of girls worldwide and addressing the barriers that limit their participation. The Biden-Harris Administration is announcing new actions to invest in young people and expand opportunities for girls. First Lady Jill Biden will host the "Girls Leading Change" celebration to honor 15 young women leaders who are making a difference in their communities. The administration is committed to ensuring that girls can pursue their dreams without discrimination or violence. They are taking steps to expand education and leadership opportunities, strengthen safety and wellbeing, and support girls in pursuing STEM education and careers through partnerships with non-profit and private sector stakeholders.